$ ABT has enormous shelf space and retail presence. $ DXCM has none. $ DXCM bulls make a great deal of trivial 1% lead in MARD rates, but have little to say on the absolutely dominant position $ ABT has in mass market product distribution and marketing.

What tech growth is left for $ DXCM? 9% MARD in 2015 and in 2018...9% MARD. The wall has been hit. From here on out the gap between $ MDT, $ ABT, and $ DXCM only closes. The gap is already trivial. $ ABT has a 10% MARD already. Waiting to see what the Freestyle Libre 2 will be. (4/n) pic.twitter.com/ZvXkRuL6IH

See Pedialyte, Ensure, Glucerna, etc. See the Freestyle Freedom Lite. As the technology matures $ ABT will continue to dominate in developing products at price points that support mass-adaptation. Forced price declines will outstrip user growth for $ DXCM. (9/n)

It will not be a market of one or two vendors with products charging $500 monthly. It will look like the finger stick market. $ DXCM business model is ill-equipped for that type of scenario. Conversely, $ ABT excels in those types of markets...(8/n)

Whats overlooked is long-term significance of $ ABT - with a $140 market cap and > $2 Billion annual R&D spend means for medium and long-term. From Libre 1 to Libre 2 - this is very rapid product development. The gap in tech will close within a few cycles.
